{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e39079ca-2f6c-400e-8f7a-775de44e2bce","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit embeds the skip reason in the test attribute itself rather than using a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aec68d12-32d1-4646-8e39-72d9f8ec81e0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":296,"requestId":"9C44:113D23:163D455:18E4FD0:69F86329"},"id":"a9af04bf-b3f1-4e09-a858-f11c5680fc2a","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:13:19.723Z","parentId":"282e31fb-e6b6-4e0d-b3e3-b7da8c9b9a9a"}
